ng and excluding Lyman-alpha data. We also find that the\ngrowth index gamma parametrization cannot be applied in a simple way to the\ngrowth in Szekeres models, so a direct comparison of the function f to the data\nis performed. We conclude that the Szekeres models can provide an exact\nframework for the analysis of large-scale growth data that includes\ninhomogeneities and allows for different interpretations of observations.\n(abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Dec 2012 04:41:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-12"}
